CDs of important Monroe County record books are now available.  Each page of dozens of Monroe County record books have been photographed and made into CDs.  For a current list of available CDs click here.

 

 

 

 

Monroe, Belmont, Noble & Pickaway County, Ohio Record Books Available on CDs

 

Click here to go to list of available CDs

Click here to go to Bottom of Page

Click here for a printable CD Order Form

 

 

A special project has been initiated to make important historical records of Monroe, Belmont, Noble and Pickaway Counties, Ohio available to researchers and to the general public at a reasonable price.  Entire record books have been photographed and put onto CDs.  Every detail of each page and of each record has been captured in the photos of these record books.  By working with these CDs every detail of information is at your fingertips.  In most cases, the price of each CD is far less than the cost to travel to the respective County Courthouses.  The high pixel photography used in these photos provides outstanding reproduction of each page.  In most cases, using the enlargement or zoom feature of your computer results in the ability of figure out handwriting easier than from the original document.  And, all this can be done in the comfort of your own home, on your own time-schedule, and using nothing more than the CD-ROM drive of your own computer.

 

Click here for a description of the record books that are available on CDs.  You can also click on the title of each book/CD in the list below to be taken to a description of that book/CD.

 

CDs of these valuable record books are available from the Monroe County Historical Society (MCHS).  Orders can be placed by sending a letter containing the order form and your check to either of two locations below: (a printable order form is available by clicking  CD Order Form)

 

Monroe County Historical Society

P.O. Box 538

Woodsfield, Ohio 43793-0538

 

Phone:  740/472-1933

e-mail:  moncohissoc@att.net  

 

For a more rapid response you can order directly from the supplier at the

following address.  MCHS still gets the income from all orders.

 

Richard Harrington

9517 Mt. Vernon Landing

Alexandria, VA   22309

 

Phone:  703/780-9109

e-mail:  RichardHarrington31@gmail.com

 

Be sure to include your full name, full mailing address including zip code, phone number, and e-mail address (1).  Your check or money order should be made payable to the Monroe County Historical Society or to R.E. Harrington depending on which address you send your order.  (Sorry, we cannot accept credit cards.  Please do not send cash.)  Please understand that we cannot ship your CDs until payment has been received.  CDs will normally be shipped within 7 to 10 working days for orders sent to the MCHS.  They will normally be shipped within 1 to 3 working days if ordered from R.E. Harrington.

Key:

 

          CDs currently available

MRPP = Marriage Records per Page

SoD = Spirit of Democracy

SoD-S = Spirit of Democracy Sentinel combined February 18, 1926 (Sentinel established 1906)

MCR (-SoD) = The Spirit of Democracy and the Monroe County Republican were both published

this year and were identical except for the name on the paper.

 

*          Even though the book cover shows the inclusive dates for this book to be 1891 through 1899, the birth records contained in the book actually run from 1891 to 1903.

**        Marriage record books 4 and 5 have been combined.  The price of the combined book is $13.50.

***      Marriage record books 15 and 16 have been combined.  The price of the combined book is $13.50.

****    Because of privacy concerns the production of CDs for these books has been delayed.

+              Each page has about 45 names of deceased Monroe County residents.

++       These CDs are in PDF format.  Click here for step-by-step guidance to download Free copy of PDF reader.

+++     Several months missing Available periods: Dec 22, 1849; Jan 9, 1850 thru March 20, 1850; Dec 4, 1850 thru Jan 1, 1851

Note (1)   The CDs of record books are prepared from photographs of pages from the actual record books.  Some of these books have an index of their contents.  Other books are subdivided into sections according to the alphabet.  The CDs include the index where they are available and the alphabetical organization is preserved for those books that do not have an index.  In the future (over the next 2 years) we expect to construct a computer searchable index (CSI) for many of the record books.  This will greatly enhance the value of the CDs to researchers by allowing your computer to do the searching (by name) for you.  Because the present CDs do not have a CSI we plan to offer to purchasers of the presently available CDs, an upgrade (at cost about $3.50) as the CSIs become available.  Please include your e-mail address so that we can notify you when these upgraded CDs are available.  Your e-mail address will be secure with us.  We do not sell or otherwise compromise the security of clients personal information or e-mail addresses.

Note (2)  Ohio residents please add $0.70 for each CD purchased to cover Ohio and county taxes.  CDs cannot be shipped until payment has been received.

Note (3)  Price includes shipping and handling.

Note (4)   While not a CD, the book titled Highlights in the History of the First United Methodist Church of Woodsfield, Ohio written by Elizabeth Ogden and John Ogden is recommended as a companion to the Woodsfield Methodist Church CDs.  It is a defining book that provides extensive background for the CDs.  The book is an exciting story of dedicated ministers, abolitionists, a congressman who was an eyewitness to the Lincoln assassination, a female POW during the Civil War, and many more.   This 215 page, soft-bound book sells for $28.50.  The CD order form can also be used to order this book.

Note (5)   Personal Property Tax

Note (6) Real Estate Tax

Note (7) author, Lena Louisa Kahrig Gatten Pettit

Note (8) This CD of Index of Will Books is no longer available on CD.  Instead, the indices of all 23 will books that have been put onto CDs are now on the website at:  http://freepages.history.rootsweb.ancestry.com/~harringtonfamilies/Will%20Book%20Indices.htm
